			>
			<P>I am very happy to see that you folks are indeed listening =)</P>
<P>After reading almost every post here and looking at the other class posts (not as thorughly) I feel the biggest gripe is that Monks dont bring anything of note to a group / raid anymore.&nbsp; Other classes out shine us as Pullers and Dps, and we have the biggest glass jaw ( we die real easy even when compared to some casters)&nbsp; We would like to be needed/useful again. The reality is that what a monk can do can be replicated by other classes, while those classes still retain their original uses (cleric can pull and heal, chanters can pull/CC, Rangers can DPS , snare and give some buffs etc etc)&nbsp; Those of us that play monks probably are more fanatical about our class (tho there are less of us I think) than any other class.&nbsp; We used to be THE choice for pulling and #2 for DPS and I know I was stoked to be a monk during those times.&nbsp; </P>
<P>The AC/damage mitigation Nerf Really hurt....You asked us to stay from fix suggestions so I will say no more on that topic</P>
<P>What&nbsp;will &nbsp;you do to make us useful again? What will you do to make a monk a sought after class for raids and groups?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Again thank you for your response I know I certinaly feel much better knowing that you folks havent forgotten us =)</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Minymoto the insane Monk =)</P>
