			>
			<DIV>Monks used to be quite self suffcient, they could survive without as much need for armor or weapons and&nbsp;they could self heal. Today monks are as equipment dependant as every other class, and with the mobs in PoP and GoD, we get hit so hard the self healing is more of an emergancy heal than a downtime reducer or something to help with prolonged combat.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'd think monks should be more self suffcient again. They shouldn't need as as much attention from the support classes. There was an idea aired by a dev on monkly business about turning back a mob's riposte onto itself (as long as the monk wasn't tanking), which would help us in this aspect, and also help with positioning a mob, as currently all the melee want to be stuck behind the mob so they don't take damage from ripostes.</DIV>	
