<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&message.id=314#M314">5</a> of 288
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1223 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Thanks for taking the time to ask and listen, Brenlo.  In case you or SoE end up getting flamed at some point in this thread, I wanted you to know up front that your attention is appreciated!<br><br>What is broken?  I'm not sure whether you mean truly broken, or issues that should be addressed because they seriously detract from monk game play and class balance.  I'll take a fairly broad perspective, and let you pick and choose.  This is off the top of my head, so items are in random order.<br><br>(1) Monk defensive abilities are extremely weak in the post-Luclin era:  Mob ATK and DPS have scaled up tremendously, while parses indicate that our AC soft cap was locked in assuming Velious and Luclin mobs.  AC upgrades beyond early PoP/ornate level armor provide miniscule benefit to monks, so we cannot take hits.<br><br>(2) Monks are unable to solo (and barely duo) effectively beyond Luclin:  We have effectively no ability to do ranged damage (and no ability to root/snare anyway) and cannot stand toe-to-toe with post-Luclin mobs due to (1).  Given that monks are far from the most sought after classes for groups, many monks have a hard time XPing.<br><br>(3) Monks bring little utility to groups/raids:  The recent addition of the Phantom line of abilities has helped , allowing us to resume our role as a good puller (still not as good as bards, but at least we can outpull rangers/clerics/enchanter/paladins in many/most situations).  However, as pure melees who cannot tank (see (1) plus the quite reasonable restriction that we cannot grab or maintain aggro) and do far less dps than rogues (let alone casters), we are at a serious disadvantage when it comes to getting groups.<br><br>(4) The 2HB animation is so so sad -- we poke people in the tummy.<br><br>(5) Monks are utterly useless against serious AE mobs:  Since monk ranged damage is effectively zero, we contribute NOTHING against mobs with unresistable/huge AE effects (most mid-to-late PoP raid targets).<br><br>I'm sure there are plenty of other things that others will bring up, but there's a starter list.  I know you asked us not to post suggestions for fixes, but here are some ideas (hardly unique) that I think would help a lot w/o making us uber mensch or distorting balance.<br><br>(A) Tune the monk AC soft cap so that it scales with new content/mobs:  Well-equipped monks now have visible AC/HPs well below their plate-wearing comrades, so the low low low soft cap on useful ac has outlived its purpose.  No other class's usefulness would be seriously impacted by a significant increase in the monk soft ac cap, but it would let us pull more effectively, solo/duo more effectively, and in a desperate pinch tank in XP groups in non-uber zones (where we'd still be a far below par choice since we cannot hold aggro worth a damn).<br><br>(B) Give monks an insane amount of strikethrough when they are not at the top of the mob's hate list:  SoE has given monks some nice abilities to help position mobs (e.g., Dragon Punch).  Letting monks truly attack from any angle with only minor loss in dps would make monks premier mob positioners (other than swarm pets being used to corner mobs).  It would also improve effective (but not peak) monk dps because we would not lose dps when not behind the mob.<br><br>(C) Make monks immune to rampage damage (meaning they are never rampage targets, not that they mitigate rampage damage 100%):  This probably sounds crazy, but if you think back to the monk nerf, a major reason monks were nerfed was because elite monks were such effective rampage tanks.  This change would make that impossible, and also make monks able to do more than sit and cheer against AE rampage mobs.<br><br>Thanks again for listening.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
