			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&message.id=317#M317">6</a> of 288
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1223 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I'm lvl 65 with 400aa's, I have lots of PoTime items and 3 quarm loots. Want to know the stats on my range item?&nbsp;5 str / dex / agi and 3 sta... oops, how could I forget the&nbsp;5 poison resist!&nbsp;I haven't upgraded my range item HP since I was lvl 1. Why? Poor itemization&nbsp;or lack of pulling abilities. This is the 1 thing that annoys me the most, but also makes me look forward to WoW even more with every passing day. PLEASE, give me (other monks aswell if you want) a skill / disc to aggro a mob, 150 - 200 range is fine, make it increase as you level for all I care. I don't even care how you implement it, imagime a monk spitting at a mob, or shouting abuse at him from a certain range, or using his jedi mind skills to get his attention, whatever.&nbsp;Just stop forcing me to use a damn 0hp range item.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>AC softcap of around 1350, I like it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Why? Because it means I don't give a crap about my AC. I run around on raids with 50 or 60 weight. I'm currently looking for a UI that doesn't show AC. You could either reverse the mitigation nerf which is no longer needed, you know it, we know it. Increase the softcap while your at it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This may actually make me care about the weight limit, what was it again? 24?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Remove ripostes, make me automatically riposte a riposte, I have to have my own botted cleric healing me to counter for riposte damage. I do this to stop mobs from getting pushed too much, stand infront and chain cast dragon punch. No, not just while you don't have aggro, I don't want ripostes even when I'm tanking. I tank alot, simply because it's more efficient for me to tank while the casters do their stuff, stop the clerics from wasting even more mana trying to keep me healed, k?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>To sum it up with 3 simple points:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1) Allow me to aggro mobs without using a range weapon (ie, like a warrior can with incite)</DIV>
<DIV>2) Remove the mitigation nerf which lost it's usefullness years ago. Increase AC softcap.</DIV>
<DIV>3) Remove riposte's.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Do those 3 things and I might actually enjoy EQ a bit more.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks for your time.</DIV>	
