	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=15768'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>superchum</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 53<br>
				
				Registered: 03-29-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=15768'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&message.id=286#M286">7</a> of 288
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1223 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Things that are broken about the monk class (or as I like to call it, 10 things I hate about you):</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>1- Purify Body refresh timer. Purify Soul had its refresh timer reduced many many patches ago. Purify Body has not had its refresh timer touched. The cleric and monk version cost the same amount of AA and the same amount of AA to upgrade through the PoP upgrade. The refresh timers should be equal.</P>
<P>2- Return Kick. This AA has been broken since Luclin was launched. It and Double Riposte are pretty meaningless to begin with, due to the fact that only the main tank stands in front of most monsters these days, but even so, Return Kick could use some looking at.</P>
<P>3- Animations. 2hb animation is really really bad. As is the whole Tail Rake fiasco (one of the truly uniquely Iksar aspects of Everquest was pretty much ruined by Luclin animations and the Dragon Punch AA).</P>
<P>4- Monk Itemization.</P>
<P>4a- The Weight of Gates of Discord Monk armors is extremely high. That needs to be fixed. Even the monk class only armor is too heavy. The monk class still does have an AC penalty for going overweight. And Packrat supposedly doesn't affect that portion of weight.</P>
<P>4b- The Monk mitigation nerf was done, according to the patches (see one of my other posts for the long winded details of those patches) mostly due to the large amount of "All/All items" that proliferated Everquest during Velious and Luclin. Well that itemization issue, to justify the nerf, needs to continue. Which means Monks need to have 125 AC BPs and 100 AC pants. Or else the monk mitigation nerf is simply stacking a penalty onto an itemization issue that doesn't exist.</P>
<P>4c- Monk DPS through weapons is extremely poor in the areas of the very mudflated levels of 55 to non-raiding 65.&nbsp; The market is basically filled with things like War Marshall's Bladed Staff, Copper Hammer of Striking, Windblade, etc., etc., etc. Whereas monks are still scraping to nab Golden Wraps of the Compact/Waning Light Katar, or Staff of Flowing Water. For a class that is supposed to be DPS oriented, the gap at that "level" of the game is pretty small between them and the rest of the world. Rogues, at least, still have backstab to keep them ahead.</P>
<P>5- Monk relative DPS. Warriors, Rangers, Berserkers all parse very very close to monks in DPS. Whereas Rogues parse out well ahead of the rest of the pack. The relative gap is distorted. Here's a nice little reference thread: <A href="http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=3803" target=_blank>http://www.thesteelwarrior.org/forum/showthread.php?t=3803</A></P>
<P>This needs some consideration, due to the fact that monks have only two roles. That of pulling, and that of DPS. If the DPS is relatively as lackluster as it measures out to be, then the class needs to be given some sort of power in other areas to compensate. Or the DPS gap between monks and their competitors needs to be widened a smidge.</P>
<P>5a- Special Attack DPS. Frenzy is pretty darn close to Flying Kick in terms of DPS. And yet Flying Kick has never been close to backstab in terms of DPS. Why is it rogue special attack DPS can maintain such a solid, concrete advantage, but the monk special attack DPS can easily be ignored when creating new classes like that?</P>
<P>5b- Monk naked fist damage. At this point in the game, you'd do well to put monk fist damage back to what it was on Planes of Power release ... 18 damage, 20 delay at level 65. 15/20 is a joke.</P>
<P>5c- Monk role as best DPS from "any angle" ... it's been suggested that the class could be given some sort of riposte immunity to allow them to attack raid level monsters from the frontal arc with little to zero penalty. For a raiding monk this would be a nice little boost to relative DPS (positioning would no longer be hampering DPS as a monk could get into&nbsp;a less crowded area of the monster, as well as help even out push) and could eventually give monks a more refined or specialized raid role (that of positioning). I mention this here, because Kavhok and Rytan have mentioned it on Monkly Biz ... because it concerns monk relative DPS specifically ... and because Return Kick being as broken as it is, would mean that the ability, if put live to test, would turn out to be affected by the broken-ness of Return Kick and Double Riposte. So keep that in mind. I also bring it up because the description of Monks being the best DPS from "any angle" is a broken description. That's not the way everquest functions. DPS crowds the backs of monsters, due to monster defenses being lower from back there, and due to ripostes and other nasty things like Area Effects not affecting the back arc in many situations. The risks for standing anywhere but behind a monster is simply too high, so monks being the best DPS from angles besides the back, is simply a joke in terms of actual gameplay.</P>
<P>6- Planeswalk. Its duration is so short and its endurance cost is so high and its refresh timer is so long, that its effect is simply not worth ever clicking. Make this movement speed increase stack with all other movement speed buffs, and it'd be worth the cost in endurance and refresh. And its short duration would make sense. Make it work like Speed Focus or Hundred Fists in that it will stack with anything and everything. Let it actually be a monk's "run for your life!" discipline. Because in its current form, it's broken.</P>
<P>7- Monk mitigation. Parses reveal that monk mitigation is not only poor, but laughably poor. This thread here: <A href="http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=45252.topic" target=_blank>http://pub147.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showMessage?topicID=45252.topic</A></P>
<P>That thread reveals a pretty low "soft" cap on monk AC. This is bad for the game from a designer standpoint. Why? Because new armor is simply not needed for any other statistic besides hit points.&nbsp; It makes itemization a serious issue for monks. Armor class is basically meaningless for the class.</P>
<DIV>8- Monk epic. It has no Endurance on it. The Berserker Epic does. That needs to fixed. In fact, all MELEE only epics need endurance added. Endurance is, after all, a melee centric concept.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>9- Feign Death failure rate. It's a long-standing joke among the class. At 200 skill level, one should not fall to the ground as often as one does.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>10- Leather armor graphics. Since monks became tied to the beastlord and druid classes in the great "clumping" of armor types, all the armor has ended up being the leather graphic (as there is no robe models for halflings or trolls and ogres ... and the monk specific armor set is obviously only on humans and iksars). There are no more robes. There's no more gi's. There's no more fist "wraps" or wrist "wraps" ... there's no more pants that look pants, just the little leather knickers. The class already has a hard enough time carving out its own niche and identity, but the graphic presentation of the class is so horrendously common, that we simply blend in, looking like a human druid most of the time. This is a far cry from the days of monks with slick tatooed chests or long flowing robes of the lost circle. Sleeper's Tomb should not be the last place a monk could ever loot a "robe."</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-Wubao, Povar Transcendant</FONT></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-06-2004</span> <span class=time_text>05:06 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
