		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>"This needs some consideration, due to the fact that monks have only two roles. That of pulling, and that of DPS"</P>
<P>I guess this is another one of those "how do you play your monk" question.</P>
<P>My monk is a pulling dps tank. I tank because I find it fun, am I good at it? Hmm, not really but with enough clerics behind you anyone can tank if they have enough HP. I tank in PoTime, I tank some of those big nameds during the fennin script. I'll battle warriors / SK's for aggro every now and then just for a bit of fun =)</P>
<DIV>So please don't forget that some monks actually play to tank aswell. Only thing going for me in the tanking department is I have fairly decent HP and with 3 stun procs I'm not too bad at getting aggro. No where near as good as a warrior with equal potime weapons though, but enough to have some fun every now and then.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Could definatly use some help though =( /cough mitigation nerf /cough</DIV>	
