			>
			<DIV>Honestly... Wubao said pretty much everything I would have.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The only things I would add:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Until PoTime the best ranged 'weapon' we get is: </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Shissar Fangs. 5str, 5dex, 3sta, 5agi, 5svPoison. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Compared to:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Featherwood Compound Bow (Bazaar buyable) that has 10ac, 10 sta, 15 wis, 15 agi, 35 magic resist, 100hp, 100 mana and an archery mod.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>as well as:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Stonewood Compound Bow (Again Bazaar buyable) has 10ac, 15str, 10sta, 15int, 100hp, 100mana, 35svDisease, AoB, and an archery mod.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Both bows are never 'used up' and offer excellent stats while also offering the ability to do ranged damage. There is really nothing that compares to this for monks until PoTime, which is silly.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>B.) </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The monk weight limit now serves no purpose, and is an un-needed penalty for monks. Before this was intended as a balancing feature due to monks not being as equipment dependant as other classes. Now it is just a pain due to monks being just as dependant on equipment as every single other class in the game.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
