<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&message.id=245#M245">19</a> of 288
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1223 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I support all of Wubao's (Superchum) points 100%.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Adding to that a few arguements.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Pulling</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>What was once a vital task, has become rather trivial (Mob positioning, easy encounters in 90% of the game to handle multiple mobs). This is not a bad thing, since pulling wasn't a planned feature for everquest, but it was the niche for monks. Now that there's&nbsp;rarely a&nbsp;demand for specialised pullers, monks are now more reliant on damage dealing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Damage dealing.</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>Wubao adressed this, due to itemization and the fact that a lot of other classes peak early, monks stay behind on the DPS market. Not only Rogues and Wizards outdamage monks as intended, but a lot of other classes outdamage the majority of monks because they peak much earlier due to spells/tradeskilled bows or pets. In other words, monks "need" Plane of Time/elemental weapons to match up to other bazaar geared classes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This and the fact other classes bring more usefull extra's to the table (pulling has become mainly trivial remember?) causes monks to be one of the most innefficient classes (Save for beserkers, they need love too<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>) to invite to a group, unless they're in an Elemental+ guild. And even when they have access to elemental+ gear, they still suffer the reputation of pre-elemental monks as the majority dictates how a class is perceived.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Mitigation disparity</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>New content and their rewards have not been designed to account for the induced mitigation disparity&nbsp;on monks. This mitigation penalty is outdated as are the items which caused developers to evaluate the monks defensive capabilities.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>ps. Will there be more revamps of old world zones to balance&nbsp;content to new expansions? This is a semi monk issue concerning pulling and perhaps itemization.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=102627"><img src="http://www.xs4all.nl/~siljeon/greyborne.gif" border=0></a><br><a href="http://www.brellrants.net/brell">Brell</a> - <b>There are no mistakes, only consequences</b> - <a href="http://www.exemplarboards.net/">Exemplar</a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
