<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&message.id=244#M244">20</a> of 288
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1223 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I feel monk DPS and pulling abilities are pretty much where they should be after the melee balancing.&nbsp; Monk defense is still off, and there's only one reason; the mitigation nerf.&nbsp; All the stated reasons for its implementation when first patched in no longer apply/exist, yet the penalty is still there.&nbsp; Even with 220+ AAs (all defensive AAs maxed out), I still take damage 3-4 times as fast as a WAR/PAL/SK against any mob tougher than an LDoN normal.&nbsp; In GoD any single trash mob in a level-appropriate zone can take me out in &lt;15 seconds.&nbsp; That should not be happening.&nbsp; Monks were originally designed to be effective, if secondary, tanks.&nbsp; Now with the mitigation nerf, plus the rebalancing of new all/all and MNK/DRU/BST items coming out, plus the nerf by omission of not giving monks various new defensive AAs when expansions come out, etc., monks' defense has been totally gutted by over-compensation for a perceived problem from years ago.&nbsp; Monks, as designed, were supposed to fight toe-to-toe with mobs; they were given an innate AC bonus to give them AC similar to plate classes, they were given Mend to allow them to basically tank mobs like a warrior, but only on a limited basis, and they were given an even footing on defensive AAs (not including Defensive disc) and hitpoints with Kunark's release.&nbsp; The intent was very clear...monks were supposed to be viable secondary tanks.&nbsp; Many thousands of monks were created under this premise, and it was and is just flat out wrong to pull the rug out from under them.&nbsp; With equivalent defensive AAs, int caster classes&nbsp;can literally out-tank monks with rune effects&nbsp;or lifetaps.&nbsp; This is&nbsp;just not balanced.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If the combination of&nbsp;"secondary" DPS, "secondary" tanking, and "primary/secondary" pulling (depending who you talk to) is deemed too powerful and the status quo of secondary DPS, poor/no tanking, and primary/secondary pulling (only recently have we gotten this role back close to the top, btw) is deemed appropriate (I can't see why it should given where some other classses stand in the rungs of these 3 ladders, but you asked for no direct class comparisons), then you should at least give monks some flexible way of increasing their defensive abilities at the cost of DPS.&nbsp; That way I can still fulfill the role I created my monk to fill, and not be a poor DPS rogue with FD as I am today.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
