<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&message.id=243#M243">21</a> of 288
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1221 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>1, Parses that seem to indicate a lack of progression for in game achievements, via an AC 'soft cap' that seems&nbsp;most severe&nbsp;to monks. Whether it is true or not, we do not 100% know, but its something we have seen evidence for and would like to see answered.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2, Due to taking a high distribution of&nbsp;near max&nbsp;hits, and those hits with the Expansions since PoP with trash creatures in raid encounters,&nbsp;routinely hitting for&nbsp;1400+&nbsp;I feel we are quite possibly the worst class at&nbsp;standing toe to toe&nbsp;available in the game, a place I don't think we deserve to be at all. (I can elaborate further on this, as to why, why healing us is harder, why staying alive against spikes is harder and so forth)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3, Considering our position as the worst possible tank,&nbsp;what use is the&nbsp;weight penalty or the 'innate' monk bonus AC.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4, Parses that show that each class avoids hits thru Armour Class at exactly the same level. Which would go against the idea that Plate armour absorbs better, but avoids less, while the Leather armour absorbs less but avoids more.&nbsp; Only our superior Block skill over the&nbsp;Parry skill&nbsp;allows us to block more hits, but this is a monk skill, it is not a Leather skill.&nbsp; To me using block, would be no better then using Feign Death, well we can Feign Death and avoid all incoming hits...comical tho it is, I don't think its a valid answer. One is based on Armour Class and the type of armour, the other is based on class specific skills.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5, Feign Death. With the ability to lose aggro being spread around, with not only new classes recieving the ability, but older classes getting revamped and very much more powerful versions of theirs, I feel that Feign Death has lost a lot of its relative power. To understand this I would say by choosing a monk you give up a lot, all magic using and no specialization. Warriors take the damage, Rogues deal the damage, of the three melee we are least speciialized. In return you recieve Mend and Feign Death.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It would be foolish to say the skills are not powerful, both are, and I would say that Mend has scaled nicely, I do not think that Feign Death has. Stonewall has taken it a step in the right direction, but I think it needs an immeadiate memwipe component, whether it be AA or another innate ability usable every two minutes,&nbsp;to be on a par with other skills that have grown or been granted.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
