		" 
			>
			While "ability to solo" might not be a "class balance" issue, I think you'll find as you ask other classes what they think is most broken that every class would LOVE to have the ability to solo.  Finding a group and getting to your night's hunting ground takes time, which means that classes that cannot solo (clerics, warriors, rogues, monks, berserkers, and paladins) cannot log on, play for an hour, and log off unless they want to spend their time tradeskilling or something like that.  I don't think any of those classes want to solo like bards, wizards, druids, enchanters, or necros (well, we'd love to, but we gotta start somewhere), but it would make the game a lot more enjoyable to be able to play in small bursts when we can't allot several hours at a time.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-06-2004</span> <span class=time_text>06:12 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
			>
			
				&nbsp;
				
				<br><br><a href="javascript:lipopup('/eq/notification?board.id=monkbalance&message.id=237&notification.type=1', 'notification', 600, 460, 'yes', 'yes')" class=text_smallest><u>Report Abuse to a Moderator</u></a>
				
		</td>
			
		</tr>
	</table>
	
		











	







